{% schema %}
  {
    
    "name": "Section 5",
    "tag": "section",
    "class": "gps-585931379100025691 gps gpsil",
    "settings": [{"type":"paragraph","content":"Section design by GemPages. [Click here to start design](https://admin.shopify.com/store/1wi06b-ei/apps/gempages-cro/app/shopify/edit?pageType=GP_STATIC&editorId=585931378814616411&sectionId=585931379100025691)"},{"type":"select","label":"Section Preload","id":"section_preload","options":[{"label":"On","value":"true"},{"label":"Off","value":"false"},{"label":"Off Lazy Script","value":"off_lazy_script"}],"default":"false"},{"type":"text","label":"Checksum","id":"checksum"},{"type":"html","id":"ggw_Ra3AKe0_text","label":"ggw_Ra3AKe0_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:32px;\"><strong>Shocking Truth: The Real Root Cause Nobody Talks About</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gga3AvmNcLj_text","label":"gga3AvmNcLj_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Most people think fast eating is just a personality quirk.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\"><strong>They're dead wrong.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Fast eating triggers something called the <strong>competitive feeding response</strong> - an ancient neurological pathway left over from when dogs lived in packs and had to defend their food from competitors.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Here's how this silent killer works in your kitchen:</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">When your dog sees food presented in any pile formation, their brain <strong>immediately switches into survival mode.</strong> They think: \"I need to consume this resource before competitors arrive.\"</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">This triggers rapid gulping motions designed to <strong>inhale maximum food</strong> in minimum time.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">But here's the deadly part: This gulping motion forces your dog to <strong>swallow massive amounts of air</strong> along with their food.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggTClWWIMus_text","label":"ggTClWWIMus_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Think of it like inflating a balloon inside your dog's stomach. <strong>These air bubbles create gas pressure</strong> that can literally flip their stomach upside down.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Once the stomach twists, <strong>blood supply gets cut off</strong>. The stomach tissue begins dying within minutes.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Even worse: The twisted stomach traps gas inside, creating more pressure that can <strong>rupture the stomach wall</strong> or compress the lungs until your dog can't breathe.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggMf3OSJ17s_text","label":"ggMf3OSJ17s_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Without immediate surgery, <strong>most dogs die within 30 minutes</strong> of stomach torsion.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">The tragic irony? <strong>Your dog's love for their food is literally killing them.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggjTxiykrTg_text","label":"ggjTxiykrTg_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:32px;\"><strong>Why Every \"Solution\" You've Tried Has Failed</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggAJeSZjh5f_text","label":"ggAJeSZjh5f_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">You've probably tried everything:</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggs6pwzYUvb_childItem_0","label":"ggs6pwzYUvb_childItem_0","default":"<p><strong>Hand feeding</strong> (exhausting and you can't leave your dog alone)</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggs6pwzYUvb_childItem_1","label":"ggs6pwzYUvb_childItem_1","default":"<p><strong>Tennis balls in the bowl</strong> (choking hazards that dogs remove anyway)</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggs6pwzYUvb_childItem_2","label":"ggs6pwzYUvb_childItem_2","default":"<p><strong>Basic slow feeder bowls</strong> (dogs \"beat\" them and still gulp)</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggs6pwzYUvb_childItem_3","label":"ggs6pwzYUvb_childItem_3","default":"<p><strong>Puzzle toys</strong> (too complicated, food gets stuck)</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg0AUHLzhPK_text","label":"gg0AUHLzhPK_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\"><strong>But we already know that's impossible when</strong> every single solution still presents food as one pile that triggers competitive feeding instincts.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Traditional slow feeders might reduce eating speed by <strong>40%</strong>, but they only reduce air intake by <strong>10% </strong>- and it's the air intake that kills.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggqYTsWulCT_text","label":"ggqYTsWulCT_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:32px;\"><strong>So What's The Solution?</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg7DhmrjA8q_text","label":"gg7DhmrjA8q_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Here's a secret not many people know:</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\"><strong>The problem isn't that your dog eats too fast.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\"><strong>﻿The problem is that their brain thinks they're fighting for survival every single meal.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">After Sophie's surgery, I spent months researching neurological feeding triggers in dogs. I discovered breakthrough research from the <strong>Journal of Veterinary Behavior</strong> showing that when food presentation is broken up dramatically enough, <strong>the competitive feeding response completely deactivates.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Instead, dogs switch into what researchers call <strong>\"foraging mode\" </strong>- the natural, calm feeding pattern dogs use when they're not under threat.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">This is how dogs are supposed to eat. No gulping. No air swallowing. <strong>No life-threatening gas bubbles.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">The technology that makes this possible is called </span><span style=\"background-color:#F5C242;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\"><strong>Neurological Reset Technology.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg2D62d6B8G_text","label":"gg2D62d6B8G_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:32px;\"><strong>The One Bowl That Actually Saves Lives</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggTXrzznih5_text","label":"ggTXrzznih5_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:18px;\"><strong>It gives the epiglottis time to properly seal between swallows.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggB55YSD-vz_text","label":"ggB55YSD-vz_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">The problem was finding this technology in a form that regular dog owners could actually use.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">That's when I partnered with Waggier, a company that's helped <strong>over 50,000 dogs</strong> transition from dangerous gulping to peaceful foraging.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Together, we developed something I now recommend to<strong> every single client: The PaceBowl Honeycomb Slow Feeder Bowl.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggCCTf7tcgj_text","label":"ggCCTf7tcgj_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">This isn't just another slow feeder bowl.</span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">The <strong>PaceBowl's honeycomb maze design</strong> breaks up food presentation so completely that your dog's brain <strong>cannot recognize it as a single resource to defend.</strong></span><br><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Instead of thinking \"I need to gulp this down before competitors come,\" your dog thinks \"I need to forage through this natural environment.\"</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\"><strong>The competitive feeding response shuts off entirely.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggADeqxdUVt_childItem_0","label":"ggADeqxdUVt_childItem_0","default":"<p>Made from <strong>medical-grade stainless steel</strong> that never harbors bacteria like plastic bowls do.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggADeqxdUVt_childItem_1","label":"ggADeqxdUVt_childItem_1","default":"<p><strong>Dishwasher safe </strong>for easy cleaning.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggADeqxdUVt_childItem_2","label":"ggADeqxdUVt_childItem_2","default":"<p><strong>Veterinarian approved</strong> by emergency vets who see GDV cases nightly.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggKh6gnagMc_text","label":"ggKh6gnagMc_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">Most importantly: <strong>It works from the very first meal.</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggpKDeg4cqA_text","label":"ggpKDeg4cqA_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:32px;\"><strong>The Results Speak For Themselves</strong></span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg0BrI_AZOM_text","label":"gg0BrI_AZOM_text","default":"<p><span style=\"background-color:transpare